+/*
+ * tkBorgOSX.c --
+ *
+ *	macOS (desktop) implementation of the "borg" Tcl command for
+ *	undroidwish.  AndroWish's borg command (tkBorg.c) is a JNI bridge to
+ *	the Android framework and is deliberately omitted from undroidwish
+ *	("AndroWish sans the borg").  This file provides a drop-in borg
+ *	command for the macOS desktop build whose subcommand surface matches
+ *	the documented Android command exactly (see
+ *	https://androwish.org/home/wiki?name=Android+facilities).
+ *
+ *	Design goals, in order:
+ *	  1. Every documented subcommand exists and NEVER raises a Tcl error
+ *	     for a well-formed call -- subcommands with no macOS analog are
+ *	     safe no-ops returning an empty string (or the Android-shaped
+ *	     "empty" value), so unmodified AndroWish/de1app code runs.
+ *	  2. Subcommands that DO map onto a native macOS facility get a real
+ *	     best-effort implementation using only system facilities already
+ *	     available to the build (libc, Tcl/Tk, CoreFoundation, IOKit,
+ *	     CoreGraphics) plus standard command-line tools (say, open,
+ *	     osascript) launched via posix_spawn.  No new hard link
+ *	     dependency on a private framework: DisplayServices (for screen
+ *	     brightness) is reached lazily via dlopen.
+ *
+ *	This is intended as a patch submittable to the AndroWish maintainer;
+ *	it is guarded for __APPLE__ and is self-contained.
+ *
+ * Copyright (c) 2026 John Buckman.
+ *
+ * See the file "license.terms" for information on usage and redistribution of
+ * this file, and for a DISCLAIMER OF ALL WARRANTIES.
+ */
+
